  "description": "V75 query-side ablation on top of v73: keep build memory, retrieval, compiler evidence context, answer model, and mechanical finalizer policy unchanged, but route generic advice/tips/suggestions/should-I questions to profile_preference and run a compact second-pass profile repair only for profile_preference. This keeps the positive signal from v51 profile repair while reducing its token cost through a smaller repair context. It is inspired by creating001's two-stage evidence-to-answer query design, SimpleMem's adequacy/reflection pass, and method.md's profile/event memory direction. It uses only question text, visible question_time, raw dialogue, retrieved Memory Context, route, draft answer, and draft JSON; no gold answer, judge output, benchmark label, sample id, qid, row index, test feedback, or sample-level rules.",
